snippet.textDisplay:
Casing and skin are different though in some applications they are interchangeable.
Most commercial hotdogs are skinless because after the flash cooking their cases are removed, whereas sausages heavily depend on the brand. The skin still behaves like a casing, but doesn't have the same chewy texture as cased hotdogs would.
You would want to remove the Skin on some of those hotdogs just for the giggles next time.
